Interface BatchProcess.AfterBatch<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - type of the object being processed
    Enclosing class:
    BatchProcess<T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface BatchProcess.AfterBatch<T>
    Lambda compatible interface that will be called after processing is complete

      boolean execute(Context context, Collection<AlexandriaException> exceptions)

    • Method Detail

      • execute

        boolean execute(Context context,
                Collection<AlexandriaException> exceptions)
         throws Exception
        Delegated method after a batch is completed, useful for logging results or saving state.
        Parameters:
        context - Alexandria context that may or may not be needed by caller.
        exceptions - Any exceptions thrown during processing, or empty list if no errors occurred
        Returns:
        False if exceptions are not being handled by the caller (triggering BatchProcess.execute(Batch, Task, AfterBatch) to thrown a BatchProcessException, or true if the errors have been handled and no BatchProcessException will be thrown.
        Throws:
        Exception - This exception will be wrapped by BatchProcess.execute(Batch, Task, AfterBatch) just like exceptions at any other phase and thrown in a BatchProcessException
